China Research Field Trip









Ben Cavender  Principal The China Market Research Group (CMR)   Ben Cavender is a Principal with The China Market Research Group (CMR), which he joined in 2006. His work at CMR focuses on market analysis, due diligence, retail strategy, brand positioning, and growth strategies in the China market.  His role at CMR includes oversight of projects for Fortune 500 companies, SMEs, and domestic Chinese companies in the e-commerce, entertainment, fashion & apparel, food & beverage, hospitality, luxury goods, and TMT sectors seeking to expand their presence in China and abroad as well as for institutional investors and their portfolio companies. He is a frequent guest on CNBC, Bloomberg TV, and the BBC and is regularly quoted in The Economist, The Wall Street Journal, BusinessWeek, and the Financial Times.  The China Market Research Group (CMR) provides multinationals and domestic Chinese companies with customized research and the strategic market intelligence that they need to make smarter decisions in China. Their clients come from a variety of industries, including Fortune 500 and leading Chinese companies, private equity firms, SMEs, and hedge funds.


 
 



Bill Maldonado  Chief Investment Officer, Asia Pacific and Strategy Chief Investment Officer, Equities HSBC Global Asset Management   Bill Maldonado is HSBC Global Asset Management's CIO, Asia-Pacific and Strategy CIO for Equities globally. Based in Hong Kong, Dr. Maldonado oversees the investment strategies in the region. He has worked in the asset management industry since joining HSBC in 1993 as a European derivative-based portfolio manager. Over the past 21 years, Dr. Maldonado has headed up a number of investment functions, such as non-traditional Investments (including passive indexation mandates, fund-of-funds, structured products and hedge funds). He became Strategy CIO, Equities and CIO for the UK in 2010. He was also involved in the management of some Asian portfolios in Hong Kong during 1993-1994.  Dr. Maldonado holds a D. Phil in Laser Physics from Oxford University and an MBA from the Cranfield School of Management.


 
 



Calvin Quek  Head of Sustainable Finance Program Greenpeace East Asia   Calvin Quek is head of Greenpeace East Asia's Sustainable Finance Program and leads its engagement of the financial community. Calvin serves on the Board of the China Carbon Forum, and was the first Executive Director of the Beijing Energy Network. Prior to joining Greenpeace, he was with Citigroup for close to a decade, with the investment research team in Singapore, and led Citigroup Singapore's CSR & Volunteerism committee in 2008. Calvin has an MBA from Peking University, and an MSc in Wealth Management from Singapore Management University.  Calvin is a regular commentator on China's energy and environmental issues, contributing to the Financial Times, South China Morning Post, and has appeared on CNBC, Bloomberg and CCTV.


 
 



Dong Wang  Chief Executive Officer HSBC Jintrust  Dong Wang is the Chief Executive Officer at HSBC Jintrust, a position he has held since November 2012. Dong joined HSBC Jintrust during its preparatory stage as one of its key founding members and was Head of International Business between April 2008 and November 2012 and Head of Finance between November 2005 and April 2008. Dong holds a Master in International Finance (summa cum laude) from the Universiteit van Amsterdam and BEng in International Trade and Computer Science (second major) from the Shanghai Jiao Tong University. He is a CFA charterholder and a non-practising member of CICPA.


 
 



Elizabeth Allen Director and Head of Credit Research, Asia Pacific HSBC Global Asset Management  Elizabeth Allen is a Director and Head of Credit Research in the Asian Fixed Income team. She has over 15 years of credit experience in the region. Prior to joining HSBC in 2011, Elizabeth worked as a Senior Credit Officer at Moody's Investor Service's corporate rating team. She was also involved in investment banking and corporate lending at Credit Suisse First Boston and Standard Chartered Bank respectively. She holds a Masters in Finance from London Business School and a Bachelor of Commerce from the University of Western Australia. She is a member of CPA Australia.


 
 



Gregory Suen Investment Director, Fixed Income HSBC Global Asset Management   Gregory Suen is an Investment Director in the Asian Fixed Income team and has been working in the industry since 2000. Prior to joining HSBC in 2007, Gregory worked as an investment manager at PCI Investment Management Limited. He holds a master's degree from the University of Hong Kong, a bachelor's degree from the University of British Columbia (Canada).He is also a CFA charterholder and a Certified Public Accountant (CPA).


 
 


 
Huaixiang Wang Director
China Academy of Railway Science
   Huaixiang Wang, a PhD in Transportation Economics, is currently a Research at the China Academy of Railway Sciences and a Deputy Director at the Institute of Transportation and Economy. Mr. Wang graduated from Jiaotong University in 1997, and has worked in the China Academy of Railway Sciences since then.  His main areas of research and expertise include railway transport costing, tariffs, technical and economic evaluation, railway reform and the railway transportation business management.  He was a key member in the research of the China Railway Line, Beijing-Shanghai high-speed railway, railway point cost system, the reform of rail freight, and several other economic researches in the use of new railway equipment.  In recent years, he has participated in the planning of the whole rail freight tariff reform program.


 
 


 
Juan Ni Huang Vice President
Eastmoney.com
  Juan Ni Huang is the Vice President at fund.eastmoney.com, the mutual fund platform owned by eastmoney.com, China’s largest financial portal listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange.  She is responsible for the online sales and promotion of mutual funds in the fund.eastmoney.com platform.  Ms. Huang has extensive financial industry experience in marketing and has worked as a financial reporter in several prominent newspaper including Xi Kuai Bao and Yang Cheng Daily News.


 
 



Kai Hu Senior Vice President, Corporate Finance Group
Moody’s Investors Service
  Kai Hu is a Senior Vice President in Moody’s Corporate Finance Group, based in Shanghai. He covers a portfolio of large Chinese state-owned enterprises.

Before joining Moody’s, Kai worked in credit risk management, trade
finance and project finance at various financial institutions, including
Citigroup and China Merchants Bank in New York and Bank of
Communications, Shanghai Pudong Development Bank in Shanghai.

Kai holds an MBA from Ross School of Business, University of Michigan, and a Bachelor of Shanghai Institute of Foreign Trade. He is also a CFA,
FRM and a member of Chinese CPA association.



 
 



Li Ma President China Cheng Xin International (CCXI) Credit Rating   Li Ma is a Managing Director at Moody's Investors Service. Since May 2013, he has been serving China Chengxin International Credit Rating Co. Ltd. as its board director, President and Chairman of the Rating Committee.  Li has worked in the financial service industry since 1997. His previous professional experience includes Vice President / Senior Analyst at Moody's, Senior Credit Underwriter at RBS and Chief Risk Officer of RBS China.  Li received his BA degree from Fudan University in China and his MBA degree from the University of Maryland in the US. He is also a CFA charter holder.


 
 


 
Liqun Zhang Senior Research Fellow
Macro Economic Research Unit
State Council Research & Development Centre
  Professor Liqun Zhang is currently a senior research fellow at the State Council Research & Development Center's Macro Economic Research Unit. He is also the Secretary General for the Center's Academic Committee.  Prof. Zhang has more than 25 years of experience in China's macro-economic policy research, including field studies, academic research studies and policy implementation studies.  Prior to his current position, Prof. Zhang worked at the National Development and Reform Commission (NDRC).  He has been on the drafting committees for the 8th, 9th, 10th, 11th, and 12th Five-year Plans.  Prof. Zhang has published three books on topics of macro economics and economic development strategies.


 
 



Lin Duan Deputy Product Director
iResearch Consulting Group
   Lin Duan has been with at iResearch Consulting Group since 2013 and is now the Deputy Product Director, responsible for big data analysis of internet industries including e-commerce, video, social media, and mobile applications.  He is responsible for the planning and market analysis of big data products and products of service industries, competitive analysis, strategy planning for new product launches, resource coordination, assisting in research and development, and execution of strategy plans to ensure smooth completion of projects.


 
 



Mandy Chan Head of China & Hong Kong Equities HSBC Global Asset Management    Mandy Chan is the Head of China & Hong Kong Equities and has been working in the industry since 1997. Prior to joining HSBC in 2009, she was the Chief Investment Officer for Greater China equities at ABN AMRO Asset Management Ltd (ultimately acquired by BNP Paribas Group). Before that, she worked at Pacific Century Insurance Investment Management in Hong Kong and TD Asset Management in Canada. She holds a Bachelor of Commerce degree in Finance from the University of British Columbia, Canada and is a CFA charterholder.


 
 



Michael Chen Senior Vice President, RMB Internationalisation HSBC Bank (China)   Michael Chen joined HSBC Bank (China) Banker Development Program in 2008. After serving in Commercial Banking as a Large Corporate Relationship Manager for over 6 years, he moved to his current role in December 2014 mainly in charge of HSBC Bank (China)'s RMB Internationalisation and Free Trade Zone initiatives . Michael has a solid background in banking products and maintains good communication with regulators including the People's Bank of China (PBOC), State Administration of Foreign Exchange (SAFE), China Banking Regulatory Commission (CBRC), China Foreign Exchange Trade System (CFETS) as well as the Free Trade Zone administration office.


 
 



Michael Zheng Head of Fixed Income, Fund manager HSBC Jintrust   Michael Zheng took the position as Head of Fixed Income from September 2011. Michael joined HSBC Jintrust as Head of Investment Advisory in October 2008 and was in charge of the multimanager research and portfolio management. Prior to that, Michael was with Allianz China life Insurance as Director of Investment Department. He graduated from Tongji University (China) with a Bachelor's degree in Engineering Project Management and a Master's degree in Engineering Economics. Michael is a CFA charterholder, FRM Charterholder and CAIA charterholder.


 
 



Montgomery Ho Deputy CEO HSBC Bank (China)   Montgomery Ho is Deputy Chief Executive Officer of HSBC Bank (China) Company Limited (“HSBC China”) and an Executive Director of the Board of HSBC China.  Montgomery joined HSBC in 1983 after graduating from university and held a number of positions in departments responsible for deposit and saving, trade, strategy and planning. He has a wealth of experience in frontline lending as well as expertise in dealing with clients in industries such as textiles, garments, toys and electronics, and packaging and printing. He also has expertise in construction business financing and property investment financing.  Montgomery was seconded to Hang Seng Bank in 2001 as a department head in corporate banking, overseeing a group of relationship managers. He returned to HSBC in 2003 and became Senior Manager Sales, Service and Channel Development in Commercial Banking. Mr Ho was Senior Manager Commercial Banking from December 2004.  Montgomery was appointed as Managing Director Commercial Banking in November 2007, overseeing HSBC’s teams of relationship managers who look after corporate customers from around the world and Greater China. He became Managing Director & Head of Commercial Banking for HSBC China in October 2010 and led his team to achieve strong business growth.  Montgomery became Deputy Chief Executive Officer of HSBC China in January 2014, overseeing the Bank’s Private Banking, Securities Services, Rural Banking, RMB Internationalisation, Network Development, Marketing, Legal, Technology & Services, and Corporate Sustainability. He is responsible for driving the international banking of HSBC’s China clients. He also has administrative responsibility for Internal Audit.  Montgomery is a Supervisor of HSBC Life Insurance Company Limited since June 2014.  Montgomery holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in History from The University of Hong Kong, and an MBA from The Chinese University of Hong Kong.


 
 



