Steve Lee Chairman and Head of China & Taiwan HSBC Global Asset Management (Taiwan)    Steve Lee was appointed Chairman of HSBC Global Asset Management (Taiwan) Limited, and Head of China & Taiwan for HSBC Global Asset Management in December 2012. Prior to his current role, he was the CEO of HSBC Jintrust in China. Steve joined HSBC Global Asset Management in Hong Kong (AMHK) in 2003 as Head of Regional Development and China Business and was appointed an Executive Director of the AMHK Board of Directors and a member of the Asia Business Executive Committee. He was seconded to China in 2005 to set up and lead HSBC Jintrust, a joint venture between HSBC Global Asset management and Shanxi Trust Corporation, headquartered in Shanghai, China. Steve has over 15 years experience in the Greater China Region including a four-year stint in Taiwan, working for JP Morgan Taiwan (formerly Jardine Fleming Taiwan) and later JP Morgan Hong Kong as Head of Business Development. In this role, he was responsible for JP Morgan's China joint venture projects as well as other regional business development initiatives. He obtained his Master degree in Economics from the University of Houston and is fluent in English, Mandarin and Cantonese.


 
 



