            HSBC Global Liquidity Products Overview  > 

        

            HSBC Global Liquidity Products Overview
        


            HSBC NTD Money Market Fund


            HSBC NTD Money Market Fund
        





               HSBC NTD Money Market Fund
            










Fund objective
The fund aims to diversify investment risk, ensure safety and high liquidity of fund asset and pursue stable income and long-term investment return. 
Permitted investments
Under the principle of faith and professional investment operation, the fund may invest in, but is not restricted to, domestic bank deposit or domestic short-term commercial paper (Treasury Bill, Negotiable Certificates of Deposit, paper or draft issued by companies or government institution, other short-term certificates obligation approved by Financial Supervisory Commission), securities (including government bond, corporate bond, subordinated corporate bond, bank debentures, subordinated bank debentures, beneficiary certificates or Asset Backed Securities based on Enforcement Rules of Financial Asset Securitization Act, Beneficiary Certificates of REITs based on Enforcement Rules of Real Estate Securitization Act, other bonds issued by Financial Supervisory Commission approved global financial institution), and Repo (including short-term commercial paper and securities). 
Credit rating
twAA+f is currently the highest credit rating for fixed income fund in Taiwan. The fund with such rating provides higher credit protection compared to other fixed income funds. As such, the risk of credit loss is miniscule. 



Fund details 




Fund Rating
Taiwan Ratings  twAA+f (2015.9.22) 


Fund manager
You Chen Da


Launch date
2 November 1995 


Valuation date
Daily


Cut-off time
16:30 Taiwan Time (GMT+8) 


Settlement date
Same day


Dividend policy
No dividend distributing 





The Fund has been approved by FSC; however, there is no guarantee that it is risk-free. Past performance of HSBC Global Asset Management (Taiwan) Limited does not guarantee future returns and you may not get back the amount initially invested.  Apart from exercising the duty of care of a prudent administrator, HSBC Global Asset Management (Taiwan) Limited will not be responsible for the profit or loss of the Fund, nor guarantee a minimum return.  Investors should read the prospectus carefully before subscription.  The prospectus is available by contacting intermediaries of this Fund or by clicking here.
The relevant expenditure borne by the Fund has been disclosed in the Fund Prospectus, investors can also obtain this through the Taiwan Stock Exchange’s website.
Independently operated by HSBC Global Asset Management (Taiwan) Limited 















